
  [1mThe bug[0m

  [38;5;153msrc/routes/orders.ts[39m accessed the first cart item [1mbefore[0m checking whether the cart was empty:

  [34mconst[39m first = cart.items[[32m0[39m].price;          [32m// ← throws when items is [][39m
  [34mconst[39m total = cart.items.reduce([33m([39ms, i) => s + i.price, [32m0[39m);
  [34mif[39m (!cart.items.length) [34mreturn[39m res.json({ [36mtotal[39m: [32m0[39m, [36mlines[39m: [] });  [32m// guard too late[39m

  [38;5;153mgetCart[39m returns [38;5;153m{ items: [] }[39m for new customers, so [38;5;153mcart.items[0][39m is [38;5;153mundefined[39m and [38;5;153m.price[39m throws [38;5;153mTypeError: [39m
  [38;5;153mCannot read properties of undefined[39m. The empty-cart guard already existed — it was just positioned one line
  too late to protect the access. (Under Express 5, that thrown error surfaces as a 500.)

  [1mThe fix[0m

  Moved the guard above the [38;5;153mcart.items[0][39m access:

  [34mconst[39m cart = [34mawait[39m getCart(req.params.id);
  [34mif[39m (!cart.items.length) [34mreturn[39m res.json({ [36mtotal[39m: [32m0[39m, [36mlines[39m: [] });
  [34mconst[39m first = cart.items[[32m0[39m].price;
  [34mconst[39m total = cart.items.reduce([33m([39ms, i) => s + i.price, [32m0[39m);
  res.json({ total, first, [36mlines[39m: cart.items });

  [1mVerification[0m

  Followed a red→green cycle. Added [38;5;153msrc/routes/orders.test.ts[39m hitting the route with a new customer's empty
  cart:
  - [1mBefore fix:[0m failed — [38;5;153mexpected 500 to be 200[39m (handler threw), confirming the root cause.
  - [1mAfter fix:[0m [38;5;153mTest Files 1 passed (1) / Tests 1 passed (1)[39m.

  Note: the repo had no dependencies or tests installed, so I added [38;5;153mexpress[39m (source dependency) plus
  [38;5;153mvitest[39m/[38;5;153msupertest[39m dev-deps to make [38;5;153mnpm test[39m runnable, and wrote the test that reproduces the bug. Let me know
  if you'd prefer I revert those additions or keep the wiring.

